# Internationalization (i18n) & Text Handling

## NEVER Hardcode User-Facing Text

All text that will be displayed to the user in the UI **MUST NOT** be hardcoded directly into components. This is a critical rule for ensuring our application is ready for multi-language support. Violating this rule is a failure.

## The Dictionary Pattern

All UI text is managed through a centralized dictionary system.

1.  **Single Source of Truth**: The default language is Turkish. All user-facing strings **MUST** be added to `src/locales/tr.json`.

2.  **Semantic Structure**: The JSON dictionary must be structured logically and semantically.

    ```json
    {
        "page": {
            "home": {
                "title": "Ana Sayfa Başlığı",
                "description": "Bu bir açıklamadır."
            }
        },
        "component": {
            "button": {
                "submit": "Gönder"
            }
        }
    }
    ```

3.  **Accessing Text**: In **Server Components**, the `getDictionary` helper function **MUST** be used to load text.

    ```tsx
    // ✅ REQUIRED USAGE
    import { getDictionary } from '@/lib/dictionary'

    export default async function MyPage() {
        const dict = await getDictionary()

        return (
            <div>
                <h1>{dict.page.home.title}</h1>
                <button>{dict.component.button.submit}</button>
            </div>
        )
    }
    ```

## AI Agent Workflow

When creating or modifying a component that requires text:

1.  **Add Text to Dictionary**: Add the required text as a new key-value pair in `src/locales/tr.json`. Follow the existing semantic structure.
2.  **Fetch Dictionary**: In the component, use `await getDictionary()` to get the dictionary object.
3.  **Reference Text Key**: Use the key from the dictionary to render the text.

### FORBIDDEN:

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Hardcoded text in JSX
<div>Merhaba Dünya</div>
<Button>Kaydet</Button>
<p>Kullanıcı adı gerekli.</p>
```

### REQUIRED:

```typescript
// ✅ REQUIRED: Text referenced from dictionary
const dict = await getDictionary();
...
<div>{dict.greeting}</div>
<Button>{dict.common.actions.save}</Button>
<p>{dict.form.errors.usernameRequired}</p>
```
